data.name: L4D2 Rooftop Testing (ZWV WIP)
data.summary: A WIP port of Mercy Hospital Rooftop from L4D2's No Mercy Campaign. Play with ZWV/Co-Op, expect messy Zombie AI. Map is no longer being worked on for the time being.
data.description:
I've decided that I will no longer be updating this map for the foreseeable future. I've lost interest in mapping for Pavlov since the game's playerbase is dying on PC. If anyone has mapping experience that would like to continue development of the map from where I am with it now, please get in contact with me and provide some examples of maps you've previously made.

A port of the L4D2 No Mercy Rooftop Finale. Map is intended for ZWV.

If you want to download this, expect bugs and issues. Bot Navigation is not 100% finished yet. Play with ZWV only, spawns for DM, Infection and Hidden are not properly set up. Don't expect very frequent updates.

This is my first map, never had any experience before with map making or game development in general, but I really wanted a L4D map for ZWV. Please let me know if there's any bugs and I'll try my best to fix them. Sorry in advance for the high file size, once everything's finished I'll try my best to optimize.

If you have some experience with map making, feel free to give some advice or feedback, I could really use it.

All assets are property of Valve.


How to launch a Co-Op Zombies lobby:

  1. Select Play Online at the Main Menu.
  2. Select Create Co-Op Lobby.
  3. Select PC Only.
  4. Change the map to this map.
  5. Start the game.

 

Things to do:

- Add more spawns to accomodate for 24 player lobbies and adjust spawns for Infection and Hidden. If you ideas for where to place spawns, let me know.

- Improve Zombie AI navigation with elevation.

- Add invisible ramps for players and ZWV AI to climb over some edges.

- Optimize File Size

Issues I'm aware of:

- Messy Zombie AI, mostly them running into walls and getting stuck in places, either being caused by navmesh or the design of Pavlov's Vanilla Zombies. (Really wish zombies could climb.)

- Zombies spawning less when camping at the higher points of the map. Right now I have no fix for this.

- Everyone spawning in the same area in DM. This is intentional since the spawns are not setup for TDM/DM or other gamemodes yet. Stick with ZWV for now.

- Players able to shoot through walls. I need to set a Physmat for each material on the walls to fix this. Infection and Hidden will have to wait until this is fixed.

- Spawning out of map with some gamemodes. Some modes are not set up yet for the map, some aren't meant to be played with this map. Hidden, Infection & ZWV are the primary modes I am planning on making compatible with this map. S&D, Push, Gun Game, KOTH, TTT & CTF aren't planned for this map.

- Missing textures with new modkit. I don't know why this is happening, it's only happening with the new modkit. If anyone has had a similar issue with textures being fine in the Editor, but not in game, please tell me how I can fix this.

- Poor visuals on Quest 2. All work on the Quest 2 version of this map's on hold until I can fix the missing textures problem with the new modkit.

Do not play with Search & Destroy, you'll spawn out of bounds and into the killzone.

If you want an actual L4D2VR experience that's worth playing, go check out sd805's L4D2VR Mod, it's actually a lot of fun.

data.name: Menu Map
data.summary: A Menu Map where players can vote for next playing maps.
data.description:
Menu Map

A map where players can vote for next playing maps.

Requirements

  1. A dedicated server with file system access (You can manually create config file for server)
  2. Python 3.11, with package async-pavlov. (pip3 install async-pavlov)

Setup

  1. Edit Game.ini, make this map (UGC3189342) the only map in your server's map rotation list.
  2. Run a RCON http relay endpoint with UGC3189342/Resources/rcon.py .
  3. Create menu_config.json as ~/pavlovserver/Pavlov/Saved/Config/ModSave/menu_config.json in your pavlov server, with the following content:
{
    // RCON http relay endpoint
    "endpoint": "https://<relay_server>:<relay_port>/rcon",
    // RCON server info
    "server": "<rcon_ip_or_domain>",
    "port": 12345,
    "password": "<rcon_password>",
    // time in seconds to end vote
    "vote_round_time": 300,
    // map config, unlimited items
    "maps": [
        ["Map Display Name 1", "UGCXXXXXXX", "TDM", "https://xxx-16:9-image-to-display.png"],
        ["Map Display Name 2", "UGCYYYYYYY", "CUSTOM", "https://yyy-16:9-image-to-display.png"]
    ]
}

REMOVE // comments before use.

 

🤡🤡🤡

MOD.IO forcibly replaces HTTP to HTTPS in the description text.

"endpoint" in config is affected. Please manually edit to HTTP instead.

 

Make your own menu map

See Plugins/UGC3189342/Content/Levels/MiniMenu.umap for example

Menu Map is essentially composed of:

  1. An unique Actor inheriting BP_VoteControllerBase to control the vote process on server side.
  2. Anything to display countdown
  3. Multiple Actors inheriting BP_VoteProxyBase to display maps as an option to client side.
  4. A json config file described above

1. Copy UGC3189342 folder to your Plugins/ folder of PavlovVR-ModKit

2. Migrate Plugins/UGC3189342/Content/Blueprints into your plugin folder

Make sure these BPs are in your level.

3. Drag BP_VoteControllerMap into your level

Edit properties if needed.

4. Run RCON relay, Create config on your pavlov server. Done! Start PavlovServer now.
